The Chronicle Sports Reporter
THE Zimbabwe Universities Sports Association (Zusa) dominated athletics at the ongoing Zimbabwe Tertiary Sports Union (ZTISU) games that began at White City Stadium in Bulawayo on Wednesday. The ZTISU sports competition incorporates Zusa, Zimbabwe Technical Colleges Sports Association (TESAZ) and Zimbabwe Teachers Colleges Sport Association (ZITCOSA). Only gold medalists will proceed to the Confederation of Universities and Colleges Sports Association (CUCSA) games to be held in Malawi from August 28 to September 3. <img class="wp-image-613020 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Untitled-23-21.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Untitled-23-21.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/Untitled-23-21-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> medals Zusa collected 27 gold, 14 silver and 10 bronze medals in their 51 medals’ haul, with ZITCOSA in second spot after amassing 20 medals that included six gold, five silver and nine bronze. TESAZ only managed one gold, 13 silver and 12 bronze medals. The games are being sponsored by Delta Beverages’ Carling Black Label brand, which will reward achievers by sponsoring kits for two finalists in football, rugby, netball, volleyball and basketball for the CUCSA games.